In the Balkans there is a genre of "mysterious Orient" type stories about Germany and Austria like "my cousin said someone called the police because he flushed his toilet after midnight", "neighbors reported him for not recycling teabags by separating them into three diff bins"..
Like all of them focus on insane rules and how your neighbors go through your trash or make sure you don't make any noises at night and call the police if you do anything wrong and they fine you

"He threw a tuna can into the regular trash instead of putting the tin into the metal recycling bin and the little label paper into the paper recycling bin, his neighbor saw him do it and immediately called the police, they fined him 2000 euro for it... It's crazy in Germany..."
